devops with aws cloudplatform
------------------------------
Duration: 4/5 months
Fee: 8k
Timings: Monday - Saturday [7:10 am - 8:10 am]
                 Saturday/Sunday [7:10 am - 8:10 am or 8:10 am - 9:10 am] (if required will conduct the evening class on saturday/sunday)
Live class room notes with examples will be shared with the students on weekly basis
No recordings, no youtube and students are not permitted to record the sessions, if found anyone admission will be canceled without any fee refund

Pre-requisite:
1. Linux operating system knowledge (required)
File management commands [mkdir, ls, cd, pwd, touch, tree]
User management/Permissions commands [useradd, groupadd, chmod, chown]
Package management [apt, dpkg]
Utility [cut, sed, awk]
Process Management commands [ps, kill]

2. Shellscripting (optional)
3. Basics of java programming language (optional)
    1. how to compile and run java program
    2. java libraries and dependencies
    3. jar/war
    4. deploying an java web application on an Tomcat server
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Course Content
--------------
1. Ansible
1. What is software configuration management tools, why do we need them?
2. Understanding Ansible architecture and capabilities
3. Setting up Ansible environment
4. Ansible configuration options available
5. Inventory Management 
6. Ansible Variables
7. Basics of YAML
8. Writing and executing ansible playbooks
9. Ansible adhoc commands
10. Ansible modules 
11. Loops and Conditions
12. Ansible Vault
13. Jinja2 Templates
14. Ansible roles
15. When_Changed and When_Failed
16. Playbook execution strategies

2. AWS Cloudplatform (basic coverage)
1. AWS Cloudplatform architecture
2. Setting up an AWS Free-tier account
3. Networking (vpc, availability zones, regions, subnets, gateways (internet/nat), nacls, security groups)
4. Compute (ec2 instance, loadbalancer (alb))    
5. Database (rds instance)    
6. IAM security (users, groups, roles and access keys)    
7. Storage domain (S3 storage)    

3. Terraform
1. Introduction to IAAC automation tools
2. Terraform Architecture
3. Terraform File
4. Terraform Variables 
5. Provisioners
6. Modules
7. Terraform Statefile Management (local/aws s3 storage/dynamodb)
8. Terraform loops/conditions

Project: AWS Cloudplatform (Ansible + Terraform)
    
4. JFrog artifactory repository setup

5. Docker
1. Introduction to containerization technology
2. Virtualization vs Containerization
3. Introduction to docker
4. Docker installation
5. Docker cli
6. Docker hub registry
7. Docker Images are layered and stackable
8. Docker Directives (Image building instructions)
  1. FROM
  2. COPY
  3. ADD
  4. WORKDIR
  5. RUN
  6. CMD
  7. ENTRYPOINT
  8. ENV
  9. EXPOSE
  10. VOLUME
  11. HEALTHCHECK
  12. ARG
9. Docker Tags
10. Publishing Docker images into the docker hub registry
11. Docker networking
12. Setting up our own docker container registry (using artifactory) and publishing and pulling the images
13. Docker volumes vs Docker Bindmounts

6. Docker Compose

7. Kubernetes (25 days) 
1. Introduction to Kubernetes and why do we need?
2. Architecture of Kubernetes
3. Kubectl / Kube Config
4. kubernetes specs
  1. pod
  2. deployment
  3. service
  4. loadbalancer
  5. ingress
  6. replicaset
  7. daemonset
5. persistent volumes and persistent volume claims
6. types of controllers
7. namespaces
8. configmaps and configsecrets
9. health probes
10. resource configurations
11. rolling strategies
12. eks cluster on the aws cloudplatform
13. kubernetes networking
14. role based access (users/groups) [administration]

8. HELM

9. Jenkins (10/15 days)
  1. Why jenkins, what is the purpose of it
  2. How to setup an Jenkins cluster
  3. Installing and configuring jenkins plugins
  4. configuring global security
  5. Integrating Jenkins with git, maven, docker etc
  6. free-style project
  7. pipeline
    1. declarative pipeline (new) [main]
    2. scripted pipelines (groovy scripting) (old) #only couple of examples
  8. building ci/cd pipelines through jenkins
    1. terraform/ansible
    2. docker/kubernetes
    
10. ELK  
  1. Elastic search
  2. Logstash
  3. Kibana / Splunk
  
11. Dynatrace

Tools: [5:30 pm IST]
